# Bigtable: A Distributed Storage System for Structured Data
 OSDI 2006

# https://www.bittiger.io/videos/LPKACJnzovMKj8CB9/qtFZHdaf6JJQxyMCB
 It is a k-v store.
 1. Meta-table:
   Table0, LastKey0, Addr0;
   Table1, LastKey1, Addr1;
   Table2, LastKey2, Addr2;
 2. Table;
 3. SSTable (k-v pairs);
   a, sangpo;
   c, flyer;

 To accelerate:
   data + index
   bloom-filter

 Write into memTable (in-memory) to accelerate

 Inside GFS chunk:
  SSTable, sorted k-v pairs,
  index,
  bloom-filter

 Big Table uses a lot of memory;
 GFS uses hard-disk.
